          "id": "8022c646b3c0ec01670d5afc9845dfe25b8bafd3",
          "message": "feat(gnokey): -broadcast=true by default (#4965)\n\nThis PR replaces https://github.com/gnolang/gno/pull/3725 after\ndiscussion.\n\n* In the gnokey `maketx.go`, change the `-broadcast` flag to default\ntrue\n* In gnoweb, update `command.html` so that the help page gnokey commands\nare correct\n* Update examples in the markdown files\n* Update txtar files to remove `-broadcast` or add `-broadcast=false`\nwhere needed. (This is most of the changed files.)\n* I didn't remove the `-broadcast` flag from [this\nscript](https://github.com/gnolang/gno/blob/627790bee8346069775d3c1dc6b7861b6d84d0a4/misc/e2e/run_tests.sh#L70)\nbecause I'm not sure that it will run on a machine with the updated\n`gnokey`. (It doesn't hurt to leave the flag.)\n* I didn't change the folders `gno.land/genesis` or `misc/deployments`\n\n---------\n\nSigned-off-by: Jeff Thompson <jeff@thefirst.org>\nCo-authored-by: Morgan Bazalgette <morgan@morganbaz.com>",
